# 1. Add CSS comments in your CSS block. 
/* This is a comment in CSS */
.selector1 {
  property1: value1;
  property2: value2;
}


------------------------->


# 2. Create a page with different background-colour of a page and set an image as the 
background-image of a page

body {
  background-color: #f0f0f0;
  background-image: url('path/to/image.jpg');
  background-repeat: no-repeat;
  background-size: cover;
}


------------------------->

 
# 3. Create a different page with the width, style and color of the 4 border-style(set 
different borders on each side with different patterns). 

.selector1 {
  border-top: 5px solid #f00;
  border-right: 5px dashed #0f0;
  border-bottom: 5px dotted #00f;
  border-left: 5px double #000;
}

------------------------->


# 4. Develop a page and set the height:(in pixels and %) and width:(in pixels and %) on 
elements.

.selector1 {
  height: 200px;
}
.selector2 {
  height: 50%;
}
.selector3 {
  width: 300px;
}
.selector4 {
  width: 50%;
}


------------------------->


# 5. Develop a page with different font-styles, font-size, font-family, colors and text-align.

.selector1 {
  font-style: normal;
  font-size: 16px;
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  color: #000;
  text-align: left;
}
.selector2 {
  font-style: italic;
  font-size: 24px;
  font-family: Times New Roman, serif;
  color: #f00;
  text-align: center;
}
.selector3 {
  font-style: oblique;
  font-size: 12px;
  font-family: Courier New, monospace;
  color: #00f;
  text-align: right;
}
